#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Quick public Wi-Fi path check with mtr and whois.

Runtime behavior notes:
- The live trace is authoritative for path, sent/received packet counts, loss,
  and target reachability. Auxiliary jobs must not rewrite those counters.
- DNS, endpoint probes, public IP lookups, reverse DNS, whois, and MTU discovery
  are best-effort annotations layered on top of the main mtr stream.
- MTU discovery starts while mtr is still running, but only after the target hop
  has been observed and has five main probes. If the target is unreachable, MTU
  discovery is skipped for that address family.
- MTU discovery probes only hops that answered the main mtr. It first tries the
  interface MTU at the farthest hop; if that works, the whole responsive path is
  done. Silent hops are left blank because probing them again mostly measures
  ICMP rate limiting.
- Ctrl-C should leave the latest main display visible instead of losing it to
  the alternate screen.
"""

